{
  "stem": "150.1",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So in our ghetto, we're the only Lithuanian Jews that remained alive, plus those who had gone into the forest to fight plus those who were hidden by Gentiles.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But the numbers, there were about 225,000 Lithuanian Jews before the war.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "There were about 18,000, maybe 19,000 that survived.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So again, the coincidence of living where we lived was a very helpful thing.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Anyway, the Germans arrived very shortly-- three days after the war began, within three days.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And they issued regulations about wearing yellow stars, about not walking on sidewalks, the usual stuff.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Don't go to parks.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Don't go to hospitals.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And then they established a ghetto outside of the city in a suburb of the city.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "It was a slum.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And we were given two weeks in which the few Lithuanians who lived in the ghetto had to move out, and all the Jews had to move in.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And it was surrounded with barbed wire, and there were guards at the gates and at the fences and so on.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And it was single-family shacks, not really houses.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "There was no running water.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "There was no indoor plumbing.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "Electricity worked two hours in the morning, two hours at night, and extremely crowded.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "The ghetto authority that was established by the Germans, the [NON-ENGLISH] it was called, they controlled the living space, and everybody was allocated three square meters.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And they would check it out.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "If you had more than that, they would move in more people so that every room had at least one family, and some rooms had, you know, two or three families living there.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "As a child, you accommodate yourself.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You sort of accept things as they are.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
